In this Article

Remarks

The following tables summarize the factory methods that can be used to create a BinaryExpression that has a specific node type, represented by the NodeType property. Each table contains information for a specific class of operations such as arithmetic or bitwise.

Binary Arithmetic Operations

Node Type Factory Method
ExpressionType Add
ExpressionType AddChecked
ExpressionType Divide
ExpressionType Modulo
ExpressionType Multiply
ExpressionType MultiplyChecked
ExpressionType Power
ExpressionType Subtract
ExpressionType SubtractChecked

Bitwise Operations

Node Type Factory Method
ExpressionType And
ExpressionType Or
ExpressionType ExclusiveOr

Shift Operations

Node Type Factory Method
ExpressionType LeftShift
ExpressionType RightShift

Conditional Boolean Operations

Node Type Factory Method
ExpressionType AndAlso
ExpressionType OrElse

Comparison Operations

Node Type Factory Method
ExpressionType Equal
ExpressionType NotEqual
ExpressionType GreaterThanOrEqual
ExpressionType GreaterThan
ExpressionType LessThan
ExpressionType LessThanOrEqual

Coalescing Operations

Node Type Factory Method
ExpressionType Coalesce

Array Indexing Operations

Node Type Factory Method
ExpressionType ArrayIndex

In addition, the MakeBinary methods can also be used to create a BinaryExpression. These factory methods can be used to create a BinaryExpression of any node type that represents a binary operation. The parameter of these methods that is of type NodeType specifies the desired node type.

Properties summary

CanReduce

Gets a value that indicates whether the expression tree node can be reduced.
Conversion

Gets the type conversion function that is used by a coalescing or compound assignment operation.
IsLifted

Gets a value that indicates whether the expression tree node represents a lifted call to an operator.
IsLiftedToNull

Gets a value that indicates whether the expression tree node represents a lifted call to an operator whose return type is lifted to a nullable type.
Left

Gets the left operand of the binary operation.
Method

Gets the implementing method for the binary operation.
Right

Gets the right operand of the binary operation.

Methods summary

Accept(ExpressionVisitor)

Dispatches to the specific visit method for this node type. For example, MethodCallExpression calls the stem.Linq.Expressions.ExpressionVisitor.VisitMethodCall*.
Reduce()

Reduces the binary expression node to a simpler expression.
Update(Expression,LambdaExpression,Expression)

Creates a new expression that is like this one, but using the supplied children. If all of the children are the same, it will return this expression.

Properties

  • CanReduce

    Gets a value that indicates whether the expression tree node can be reduced.

    public override bool CanReduce { get; }

    Property Value

    • Boolean

      True if the expression tree node can be reduced, otherwise false.

  • Conversion

    Gets the type conversion function that is used by a coalescing or compound assignment operation.

    public System.Linq.Expressions.LambdaExpression Conversion { get; }

    Property Value

    • LambdaExpression

      A LambdaExpression that represents a type conversion function.

    Remarks

    The Conversion property is null for any BinaryExpression whose NodeType property is not ExpressionType.

  • IsLifted

    Gets a value that indicates whether the expression tree node represents a lifted call to an operator.

    public bool IsLifted { get; }

    Property Value

    • Boolean

      true if the node represents a lifted call; otherwise, false.

    Remarks

    An operator call is lifted if the operator expects non-nullable operands but nullable operands are passed to it.

  • IsLiftedToNull

    Gets a value that indicates whether the expression tree node represents a lifted call to an operator whose return type is lifted to a nullable type.

    public bool IsLiftedToNull { get; }

    Property Value

    • Boolean

      true if the operator's return type is lifted to a nullable type; otherwise, false.

    Remarks

    An operator call is lifted if the operator expects non-nullable operands but nullable operands are passed to it. If the value of IsLiftedToNull is true, the operator returns a nullable type, and if a nullable operand evaluates to null, the operator returns null.

  • Left

    Gets the left operand of the binary operation.

    public System.Linq.Expressions.Expression Left { get; }

    Property Value

    • System.Linq.Expressions.Expression

      An Expression that represents the left operand of the binary operation.

  • Method

    Gets the implementing method for the binary operation.

    public System.Reflection.MethodInfo Method { get; }

    Property Value

    • MethodInfo

      The MethodInfo that represents the implementing method.

    Remarks

    If a BinaryExpression represents an operation that uses a predefined operator, the Method property is null.

  • Right

    Gets the right operand of the binary operation.

    public System.Linq.Expressions.Expression Right { get; }

    Property Value

    • System.Linq.Expressions.Expression

      An Expression that represents the right operand of the binary operation.

Methods

  • Accept(ExpressionVisitor)

    Dispatches to the specific visit method for this node type. For example, MethodCallExpression calls the stem.Linq.Expressions.ExpressionVisitor.VisitMethodCall*.

    protected override System.Linq.Expressions.Expression Accept (System.Linq.Expressions.ExpressionVisitor visitor);

    Parameters

    • visitor
      ExpressionVisitor

      The visitor to visit this node with.

    Returns

    • System.Linq.Expressions.Expression

      The result of visiting this node.

    Remarks

    This default implementation for ExpressionType nodes calls VisitExtension. Override this method to call into a more specific method on a derived visitor class of the ExpressionVisitor class. However, it should still support unknown visitors by calling VisitExtension.

  • Reduce()

    Reduces the binary expression node to a simpler expression.

    public override System.Linq.Expressions.Expression Reduce ();

    Returns

    • System.Linq.Expressions.Expression

      The reduced expression.

    Remarks

    If CanReduce returns true, this should return a valid expression.

    This method can return another node which itself must be reduced.

  • Update(Expression,LambdaExpression,Expression)

    Creates a new expression that is like this one, but using the supplied children. If all of the children are the same, it will return this expression.

    public System.Linq.Expressions.BinaryExpression Update (System.Linq.Expressions.Expression left, System.Linq.Expressions.LambdaExpression conversion, System.Linq.Expressions.Expression right);

    Parameters

    • left
      System.Linq.Expressions.Expression

      The stem.Linq.Expressions.BinaryExpression.Left* property of the result.

    • conversion
      LambdaExpression

      The stem.Linq.Expressions.BinaryExpression.Conversion* property of the result.

    • right
      System.Linq.Expressions.Expression

      The stem.Linq.Expressions.BinaryExpression.Right* property of the result.

    Returns

    • BinaryExpression

      This expression if no children are changed or an expression with the updated children.
